&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;SPECIALIST MEDICINE ROTATIONAL STAFF NURSE BAND 5&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We have a fantastic opportunity for staff nurses seeking band 5 rotational posts in specialist medicine. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The rotations will be within the Division of Medicine specialist areas that include cardiology, gastroenterology, palliative, respiratory, diabetes, renal and endocrine medicines.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for highly motivated, enthusiastic and team-oriented individuals to join our specialist medicine teams, who have a passion in caring for acutely ill patients.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will have a choice of where to commence your rotation either in the cardiology, respiratory, diabetic, and endocrine, renal or gastroenterology units and t&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;here will be opportunities to obtain further training .&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This opportunity is open to newly qualified or seasoned nurses desiring a change in career or pursuing a career in specialist medicine.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you are passionate about caring, innovative, and inclusive then, come and join our reputable division, we may have just the opportunity for you!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are a warm, friendly team of professionals who work closely with members of the multidisciplinary team to provide high quality, holistic, person-centred care, that is evidence-based. We are proud of our workforce and value the diversity and creative strength of our members, and the organisation as a whole. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The education team and our PDN have structured preceptor programme for newly qualified Band 5 nurses, and various programmes including the Stepping Up, a programme to support your development. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are a warm-hearted, friendly team of professionals; our senior teams are visible on the floor, interacting, listening, teaching and supporting the team through their developments. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Join us and experience the dynamic communal working in Whipps Cross.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For an informal discussion, please contact &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Fidelia Essell-Uwagbae via email on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;f.essell-uwagbae@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
